quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  64,10,"But the unbelieving - those who gave the lie to our signs - shall be the inmates of the fire, wherein they shall remain for ever. And a wretched passage thither"
  64,11,"No mischance chanceth but by God's permission; and whoso believeth in God, that man's heart will he guide: and God knoweth all things"
  64,12,"Obey God then and obey the apostle: but if ye turn away, our apostle is not to blame, for he is only charged with plain preaching"
  64,13,"God! there is no God but He! On God, then, let the faithful trust"
  64,14,"O ye who believe! Verily, in your wives and your children ye have an enemy: wherefore beware of them. But if ye pass it over and pardon, and are lenient, then God too is Lenient, Merciful"
  64,15,Your wealth and your children are only a source of trial! but God! with Him is the great recompense
  64,16,"Fear God, then, with all your might, and hear and obey: and give alms for your own weal; for such as are saved from their own greed, shall prosper"
  64,17,"If ye lend God a generous loan, He will double it to you and will forgive you, for God is Grateful, Long-suffering"
  64,18,"He knoweth alike the Hidden and the Manifest: the Mighty, the Wise"